      "source": [
        "## 1. My lane as an ML task (type)\n",
        "\n",
        "*Classification, clustering, ranking, or scoring — which one, and why?*"
      ],
      "id": "2jWD3-Azfm8C"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "My lane, Refresh Opportunity Scoring is ranking. This is because the output my model will produce will be a queue of webpages, ranked on how urgently my model has observed that each page should be reviewed for refreshing. The model's ranking will be based on the observed performance signals of each page."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "v-mkiGD-fokn"
      },
      "id": "v-mkiGD-fokn"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PoDcU35Qfm8K"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 2. Target or proxy\n",
        "\n",
        "*What would you predict? Where does that label come from — observed outcome or a defined rule?*"
      ],
      "id": "PoDcU35Qfm8K"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "The target I would predict would be how likely a page is to need to be reviewed for refreshing. To predict my target, I would create a proxy label that measures the severity of a page's decline. This would be calculated from observations made on the page's performance signals. My proxy label could then be used to rank the pages and determine which ones should be reviewed for refresh most urgently.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7187-Tfufrie"
      },
      "id": "7187-Tfufrie"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "95uQ6N3Nfm8O"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 3. Success metric\n",
        "\n",
        "*One metric you can defend. What number means 'good'?*"
      ],
      "id": "95uQ6N3Nfm8O"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "The success metric I will use is Precision@50. This is a measure of how many pages that my model ranks in the top 50 for review priority actually need to be refreshed. If the Precision@50 value is close to 100%, it means that my model is effective at flagging pages that meet the criteria that indicate it is in decline. In addition, I have chosen Precision@50 because it provides a better reflection of how well the model ranks pages across the entire queue than using a lower precision measurement would such as Precision@20 would, which would only check if the top 20 pages my model ranks are actually in decline."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "HshTwrBnftvY"
      },
      "id": "HshTwrBnftvY"
    },
